Just now, blowfish said:

Yeah, I noticed that issue in the QuizTechAero configs.  Will be fixed.  I don't think it occurs anywhere else.

Could you show me the config you're using.  It should be copying one of the default TPR curves, maybe that part isn't working?  You've confirmed that it's only this part - other intakes work fine?

I just looked, I couldn't see any other configs with those settings.

I've configured four intakes, all four have this problem. Other intakes seem to be fine, including the stock ones I copied the config from.
  

@PART[mk1intake]:FOR[AJE]
{
	@MODULE[ModuleResourceIntake]
	{
		@name = AJEInlet
		%Area = 0.6
		#@AJE_TPR_CURVE_DEFAULTS/PilotTube/TPRCurve {}
		
		inletTitle = #$@AJE_TPR_CURVE_DEFAULTS/PilotTube/title$
		inletDescription = #$@AJE_TPR_CURVE_DEFAULTS/PilotTube/description$
	}
}

23 hours ago, Citizen247 said:

I just looked, I couldn't see any other configs with those settings.

I've configured four intakes, all four have this problem. Other intakes seem to be fine, including the stock ones I copied the config from.
  


@PART[mk1intake]:FOR[AJE]
{
	@MODULE[ModuleResourceIntake]
	{
		@name = AJEInlet
		%Area = 0.6
		#@AJE_TPR_CURVE_DEFAULTS/PilotTube/TPRCurve {}
		
		inletTitle = #$@AJE_TPR_CURVE_DEFAULTS/PilotTube/title$
		inletDescription = #$@AJE_TPR_CURVE_DEFAULTS/PilotTube/description$
	}
}

 

Hmm, that looks right to me.  Are you sure that the intake transform is pointing the right way?  It could be that you're loosing thrust because the intake doesn't see itself as being pointed into the airstream.

1 hour ago, blowfish said:

Hmm, that looks right to me.  Are you sure that the intake transform is pointing the right way?  It could be that you're loosing thrust because the intake doesn't see itself as being pointed into the airstream.

I did think about that today. I didn't make the models, I'm trying to configure intakes from the Stryker and Airplane Plus packs, but they do work fine in stock. Is stock less strict with the transform than AJE?

 

ETA:

And we have our answer! I just tested the intakes by putting them on the craft backwards, and they work fine, so obviously the transform is reversed. I'll raise a bug with the mod creators. Thanks very much for all your help.

Edited March 26, 2017 by Citizen247

On 3/26/2017 at 0:44 PM, Citizen247 said:

I did think about that today. I didn't make the models, I'm trying to configure intakes from the Stryker and Airplane Plus packs, but they do work fine in stock. Is stock less strict with the transform than AJE?

Hmm, again, nothing is obviously stands out to me.  If you can tell me exactly what part from which mod it is, I can try it myself and see if I can diagnose the problem.

6 hours ago, blowfish said:

Hmm, again, nothing is obviously stands out to me.  If you can tell me exactly what part from which mod it is, I can try it myself and see if I can diagnose the problem.

It's the various mig intakes from stryker aerospace, and the mig/saber intake from airplane plus. I imported the airplane intake .mu into blender, rotated the intake transform and exported again. the new model works properly, so it looks like you're right, the transform was backwards. I haven't tested to see if it still works in stock though.

10 hours ago, Citizen247 said:

It's the various mig intakes from stryker aerospace, and the mig/saber intake from airplane plus. I imported the airplane intake .mu into blender, rotated the intake transform and exported again. the new model works properly, so it looks like you're right, the transform was backwards. I haven't tested to see if it still works in stock though.

Good to hear that at least the cause is straightforward.  I'm less familiar with stock intakes but it should be the case that the direction of the intake is the same in AJE and stock.  Maybe the stock code depends less on the exact orientation.

Edited March 28, 2017 by blowfish

I would love this mod if it was actually working for me.

The problems i am having right now is that if i spawn with my plane. The engines are actually always turned on on full throttle. Right after spawning. No sound, no actuall thrust and no functionallity. 

I would love to fix this mod, but after some attempts. I have no idea how to. 

Also, it does not show what fuel it takes or consumpts.  It is kind strange that FAR doesn't show me center of lift.

 

Btw, i am using many more mods that 'belong' to RO.

Welcome to the forums!  Sounds like something is not working as intended, but I can't tell what just based on what you said.

The first step is to verify that you have everything installed correctly.  Make sure you're on the correct KSP version (1.2.2), and that ModuleManager, SolverEngines, and AJE are all installed and up to date.

If all that is correct, please provide KSP's log so that I can inspect it.  Instructions on how to find and upload it are in the first link in my signature.  For most of these issues, the log reveals the problem immediately (whereas it's impossible to know the issue just based on the fact that something isn't working).

https://www.dropbox.com/s/31ggrezym4qmajv/LOG.rar?dl=0 Well, everything is installed correctly. There are some addons missing that i will be downloading another time. They have nothing to do with this specific mod at all.

What is the latest ModuleMenager?

https://www.dropbox.com/s/31ggrezym4qmajv/LOG.rar?dl=0 Well, everything is installed correctly. There are some addons missing that i will be downloading another time. They have nothing to do with this specific mod at all.

What is the latest ModuleMenager?

AJE is out of date.  You have v2.7.1 but should have v2.7.3.

You also have two versions of MM.  You can delete the old one, but this probably isn't causing any issues.
